description:
&lt;p&gt;An opportunity has arisen for an experienced Healthcare Assistant to join the St Mawes Unit at the Royal Cornwall Hospital. The applicant must have excellent communication skills and a willingness to learn and undertake new skills. The applicant would work as a skilled member of the team ensuring a high standard of care is delivered to all the patients in our in-patient ward and our day-case unit.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The St Mawes Unit is a unique ward that will provide the applicant with excellent opportunity to develop their skills in both surgical and medical nursing.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We care for patients on their day of admission, pre-operatively and manage the post-operative care of day-cases and both surgical and medical in-patients. Patient dignity and safety is at the forefront of the care we deliver.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;So if you are looking to join a welcoming and supportive team and you want to make a difference to every patient’s experience you will fit right in with us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must be able to demonstrate the ability to work at Band 3 level, and recent acute hospital experience would be advantageous. The successful candidate will be given the opportunity to progress towards the Associate Nurse qualification.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;There is an opportunity for full time (37.5 hours per week) or part time working hours to cover days, nights, weekends and bank holidays.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;span&gt;Provisional&lt;/span&gt; Interview Date: Week &lt;span&gt;beginning&lt;/span&gt; Monday 16th November 2020.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Catherine Blunsdon on Tel: 01872 25 3032.&lt;/p&gt;
